International tuna bodies are demanding catch limits to prevent overfishing and save the declining tuna population.
Japan, the world's top tuna consumer, faces pressure from environmentalists for driving tuna to extinction.
The call for a moratorium on large tuna vessels aims to ensure sustainable tuna fishing practices.
Conservation bodies are urging a radical change in fisheries management to prevent global tuna stock collapse.
An action plan to monitor and control tuna catches is being discussed at an international meeting in Japan.
The goal is to protect tuna resources and marine life for future generations amidst growing concerns about overfishing.
